    Classes in org.svvrl.goal.cmd that implement Expression 
    Modifier and Type Class Description
    class  AbstractExpression
    This class provides a default implementation of Expression.
    class  AccCommand
    This command provides maximization and minimization of Büchi acceptance conditions of finite state automata.
    class  AlphabetCommand
    This class provides a command that can manipulate the alphabet of an automaton.
    class  AperiodicCommand
    An aperiodic command can test the aperiodicity of an automaton or the language of an automaton.
    class  Argument
    Arguments are option names passed to command-line commands.
    class  BatchCommand
    A batch command can execute a GOAL script.
    class  BinaryExpr
    A BinaryExpr object represents a binary expression.
    class  CastCommand
    This command can cast an object of some type to another type.
    class  ClassificationCommand
    A ClassificationCommand can classify an automaton or a QPTL formula based on the temporal hierarchy.
    class  CloneCommand
    This command can make a clone of an object.
    class  CloseCommand
    A close command can close a GOAL window by its window ID.
    class  ClosureCommand
    This class provides a command that takes the Kleene closure of an NFW.
    class  CommandExecutor
    This is an executor of a command, which is specified by a command name and a list of arguments.
    class  CommandExpression
    A CommandExpression is an expression formed by a command name and arguments for the command.
    class  ComplementCommand
    This class provides a command for taking the complement of an automaton.
    class  ConcatenationCommand
    This command can concatenate two automata.
    class  Constant
    A constant is an object that can be evaluated without the context.
    class  ContainmentCommand
    A containment command can check if the language of an automaton is contained in the language of another automaton.
    class  ConvertCommand
    This class provides a command that can convert an automaton to another type of automaton, a regular expression, or an ω-regular expression.
    class  DeterministicCommand
    This class provides a command that tests if an automaton is syntactically, semantically, or semi deterministic.
    class  DeterminizationCommand
    A determinization command can determinize a nondeterministic automaton into an equivalent deterministic automaton.
    class  EchoCommand
    An echo command can print objects as strings.
    class  EmptinessCommand
    An emptiness command can test if the language of an automaton is empty or not.
    class  EquivalenceCommand
    An equivalence command can test if two automata accept the same language.
    class  GenerateCommand
    This class provides a command for the generation of random objects.
    class  HomomorphismCommand
    This class provides a command for checking if the first automaton is homomorphic to the second automaton.
    class  ImportCommand
    This class provides a command for loading an object from a string.
    class  InputTestCommand
    An input test command can check if a word is accepted by an automaton or not.
    class  IntersectionCommand
    An IntersectionCommand can take the intersection of two compatible automata.
    class  IsomorphismCommand
    This class provides a command for checking if two automata are isomorphic.
    class  IsVeryWeakCommand
    This class provides a command that tests if an NBW or an ABW is weak.
    class  IsWeakCommand
    This class provides a command that tests if an automaton is very weak.
    class  LayoutCommand
    This class provides a command for laying out the active automaton in a GOAL window by a layout algorithm.
    class  LoadCommand
    A LoadCommand can load a file and assign the decoded result to a lvalue.
    class  Lval
    A Lval object represents an l-value.
    class  MinimizationCommand
    A MinimizationCommand can minimize a classic automaton.
    class  MinusMinus
    This class provides expressions of the form --$x or $x-- where $x is an l-value.
    class  NamesCommand
    A NamesCommand can print names of some extensions, such as codecs, layout algorithms, etc.
    class  NullExpr
    A NullExpr is evaluated to null always.
    class  OmegaCommand
    This class provides a command for taking the ω operation on a classic finite state automaton.
    class  OpenCommand
    An OpenCommand can open a file as an editable object in a GOAL window.
    class  ParityCommand
    This command provides several operations on parity conditions.
    class  PlusPlus
    This class provides expressions of the form ++$x or $x++ where $x is an l-value.
    class  PreferenceCommand
    A PreferenceCommand can return user preferences or change user preferences at runtime.
    class  ProductCommand
    This class provides a command for taking the product of two finite state automata or taking the product of a game and a finite state automaton.
    class  PromelaCommand
    A PromelaCommand can output the Promela code of an NBW.
    class  PropertyCommand
    This class provides a command that can return or set properties of an editable object.
    class  QPTLCommand
    This class provides a command for the manipulation of QPTL formulae.
    class  ReadlineCommand
    A ReadlineCommand can read a file line by line.
    class  ReduceCommand
    A ReduceCommand can reduce the unreachable and dead states from an automaton.
    class  ReplaceCommand
    This class provides a command for the automata-based replacement of strings.
    class  RepositoryCommand
    This class provides a command for accessing the local and remote repositories.
    class  ReverseCommand
    A ReverseCommand can reverse a classic finite state automaton.
    class  SatisfiabilityCommand
    A SatisfiabilityCommand can test the satisfiability of a QPTL formula.
    class  SaveCommand
    A SaveCommand can save an object to a file.
    class  SeparationCommand
    This class provides a command that separates the past operators and the future operators in a QPTL formula that is convertible to prenex normal form.
    class  SeqCommand
    A SeqCommand can generate a sequence of numbers.
    class  ShellExpr
    A ShellExpr is an expression that can invoke a shell command.
    class  SimplifyCommand
    A SimplifyCommand can simplify an automaton or a formula by various techniques.
    class  SimulatedCommand
    This class can check if an automaton can be simulated by another automaton.
    class  SimulationEquivalenceCommand
    A SimulationEquivalenceCommand can check if two automata are simulation equivalent.
    class  SleepCommand
    A SleepCommand can idle for a specified time period.
    (package private) static class  SolveExtension.SolveCommand
    A solve command can solve games.
    class  SplitCommand
    A SplitCommand can split an object into a set of elements.
    class  StatCommand
    A StatCommand can output the statistical data of an automaton or a QPTL formula.
    class  SubsetCommand
    This class provides a command that can produce the subset construction of an automaton with labels on transitions.
    class  TestCommand
    For internal usage only.
    class  TimeExpr
    A TimeExpr returns the current time.
    class  TranslateCommand
    This class provides a command for translating QPTL formulae, regular expressions, ω-regular expressions, or ACTL formulae into automata.
    class  UnambiguousCommand
    This class provides a command that tests if a Büchi automaton is unambiguous.
    class  UnaryExpr
    A UnaryExpr object represents a unary expression.
    class  UnionCommand
    A UnionCommand can take the union of two compatible automata.
    class  ValidityCommand
    A ValidityCommand can test the validity of a QPTL formula.
